-- Migration file template for adding missing repositories
-- Replace YYYY-MM-DDTHHMMSS with current timestamp in format: 2025-10-01T120000
-- This template shows how to add missing repositories to existing ecosystems

-- Example 1: Adding repositories to an existing ecosystem
-- Format: repadd EcosystemName https://github.com/organization/repository #optional-tag

-- Example 2: Adding multiple repositories to the same ecosystem
repadd "Example Ecosystem" https://github.com/example-org/repo1 #protocol
repadd "Example Ecosystem" https://github.com/example-org/repo2 #tool
repadd "Example Ecosystem" https://github.com/example-org/repo3 #wallet

-- Example 3: Adding a new ecosystem with repositories
ecoadd "New Ecosystem Name"
ecocon "Parent Ecosystem" "New Ecosystem Name"
repadd "New Ecosystem Name" https://github.com/new-org/main-repo
repadd "New Ecosystem Name" https://github.com/new-org/sdk-repo #sdk
repadd "New Ecosystem Name" https://github.com/new-org/docs-repo #documentation

-- Example 4: Real-world template for BitcoinZ (if additional repos found)
-- First, verify these repositories exist and are legitimate
-- ecoadd BitcoinZ (already exists, so skip this line)
-- repadd BitcoinZ https://github.com/btcz/bitcoinz-wallet
-- repadd BitcoinZ https://github.com/btcz/bitcoinz-seeder
