-- Example 5: Adding repositories for recently added organizations
-- Check these organizations for additional repositories:
-- 1. The Red Guild (theredguild) - added 18 repos, check for more
-- 2. Gattaca (gattaca-com) - added 17 repos, check for more
-- 3. OpenMind (OpenmindAGI) - added 6 repos, check for more

-- INSTRUCTIONS FOR USE:
-- 1. Identify the ecosystem name (must match existing ecosystem or use ecoadd)
-- 2. Verify repository URLs are correct and accessible
-- 3. Add optional tags like #protocol, #tool, #wallet, #sdk, #defi, etc.
-- 4. Use ecocon to connect sub-ecosystems to parent ecosystems
-- 5. Name your file with current timestamp: YYYY-MM-DDTHHMMSS_description
--    Example: 2025-10-01T143000_add_bitcoinz_repos

-- COMMON TAGS:
-- #protocol - Core protocol implementation
-- #tool - Development tool or utility
-- #wallet - Wallet implementation
-- #sdk - Software development kit
-- #defi - DeFi protocol or application
-- #nft - NFT related project
-- #bridge - Cross-chain bridge
-- #oracle - Oracle service
-- #dao - DAO governance
-- #explorer - Block explorer
-- #dex - Decentralized exchange
-- #lending - Lending protocol
-- #staking - Staking service

-- VERIFICATION CHECKLIST:
-- [ ] Repository is not a fork (or is a significant fork with active development)
-- [ ] Repository has recent commits (active in last 6-12 months)
-- [ ] Repository is relevant to the crypto ecosystem
-- [ ] Repository is not spam or test code
-- [ ] Repository belongs to the correct organization
-- [ ] Ecosystem name matches existing taxonomy
-- [ ] URLs are correct and accessible
